(21, 130, 'Dental Bib', 'dental-bib', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">The dental bib, a disposable protective barrier, is a crucial accessory in dental practices, safeguarding patients\' clothing from stains and contaminants during procedures. Constructed from highly absorbent materials, it effectively captures saliva, water, and debris, ensuring a clean and hygienic environment. Featuring a waterproof backing, it prevents liquids from seeping through, providing an additional layer of protection for the patient. With its adjustable neck closure and comfortable fit, it offers convenience and comfort throughout the dental appointment. Designed for single-use, the dental bib promotes infection control protocols, contributing to the safety and well-being of both patients and dental staff </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Dental bibs, also known as patient bibs or dental napkins, are protective coverings used during dental procedures to maintain cleanliness, hygiene, and patient comfort. These disposable paper or polyethylene sheets are placed over the patient\'s chest and neck area to protect clothing from splashes, stains, and debris generated during dental treatments. Dental bibs come in various sizes, colors, and materials to suit different clinical preferences and patient needs. The use of dental bibs not only helps maintain a clean and professional appearance in the dental operatory but also contributes to infection control by reducing the risk of cross-contamination between patients and dental staff.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">In addition to providing protection against fluids and contaminants, dental bibs serve as an essential component of patient comfort and safety during dental procedures. The soft and absorbent material of dental bibs helps absorb saliva, water, and other fluids from the patient\'s mouth, minimizing discomfort and maintaining a dry environment for treatment. Patients appreciate the use of dental bibs for their role in enhancing comfort and reducing anxiety by ensuring a clean and hygienic setting for dental care. Furthermore, dental bibs can be customized with features such as adhesive strips or neck ties to securely fasten them in place and prevent slippage during procedures, enhancing their effectiveness and utility.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Dental professionals prioritize the use of dental bibs as part of standard infection control protocols to mitigate the risk of cross-contamination and protect the health and safety of patients and dental staff. Proper disposal of used dental bibs following each patient encounter helps prevent the spread of infectious agents and maintains a sanitary environment in the dental operatory. Dental practices adhere to strict guidelines and regulations for the handling, storage, and disposal of dental bibs to ensure compliance with infection control standards and promote patient well-being. Overall, dental bibs play a vital role in promoting hygiene, comfort, and safety in the dental setting, contributing to a positive patient experience and optimal treatment outcomes.</span></p>', '', 1, 8, '2024-05-04 06:21:43', 748, '', '2024-05-24 02:57:35', 748, NULL, NULL, '2024-05-04 06:21:43', NULL, '{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}', '{\"urla\":\"\",\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":\"\",\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":\"\",\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}', '{\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"info_block_show_title\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_page_title\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_image\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_image_alt_txt\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_article_format\":\"standard\",\"helix_ultimate_audio\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_gallery\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_video\":\"\"}', 6, 4, '', '', 1, 0, '{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\"}', 0, '*', ''),
(22, 131, 'Dental Cotton Roll', 'dental-cotton-roll', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">The dental cotton roll is a staple tool in dental practices worldwide, indispensable for maintaining a dry field during various procedures. Its cylindrical shape allows for easy placement and effective isolation of specific areas of the oral cavity. Made from soft and highly absorbent material, it efficiently absorbs saliva and moisture, enhancing the dentist\'s visibility and control. With its non-linting properties, it ensures a clean working environment and minimizes the risk of contamination. From routine cleanings to complex restorative work, the dental cotton roll is a versatile and essential component of every dental toolkit. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Dental cotton rolls are essential items in dental practice, serving a variety of purposes to aid in moisture control, isolation, and patient comfort during dental procedures. These cylindrical rolls are made of absorbent cotton material and are available in various sizes to accommodate different clinical needs. Dental professionals commonly use cotton rolls to absorb saliva, blood, and other fluids from the oral cavity, ensuring a dry and clear field of view for accurate treatment delivery. The use of cotton rolls helps prevent contamination of dental instruments and materials, minimizing the risk of cross-infection between patients and ensuring optimal treatment outcomes.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">During restorative procedures such as fillings and crown preparations, dental cotton rolls are placed adjacent to the tooth being treated to isolate it from surrounding moisture and soft tissues. This isolation technique enhances the adhesion and longevity of dental restorations by providing a clean and dry surface for bonding materials. Additionally, cotton rolls are frequently used in conjunction with other isolation methods such as rubber dams to achieve comprehensive moisture control and isolation of the treatment area. By maintaining a dry operating field, dental cotton rolls contribute to the success and durability of dental restorations while improving the efficiency of dental procedures.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Furthermore, dental cotton rolls play a crucial role in enhancing patient comfort and safety during dental treatments. By absorbing excess saliva and fluids, cotton rolls help prevent gag reflexes and discomfort associated with moisture accumulation in the mouth. Dental professionals strategically place cotton rolls to protect delicate oral tissues from injury during procedures, such as preventing the tongue or cheek from being accidentally bitten or injured by dental instruments. Patients appreciate the use of cotton rolls for their role in minimizing discomfort and ensuring a more pleasant dental experience. Overall, dental cotton rolls are indispensable tools in dental practice, providing essential moisture control, isolation, and patient comfort to support successful treatment outcomes and promote overall oral health.</span></p>', '', 1, 8, '2024-05-04 06:24:25', 748, '', '2024-05-24 02:56:10', 748, NULL, NULL, '2024-05-04 06:24:25', NULL, '{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}', '{\"urla\":\"\",\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":\"\",\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":\"\",\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}', '{\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"info_block_show_title\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_page_title\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_image\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_image_alt_txt\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_article_format\":\"standard\",\"helix_ultimate_audio\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_gallery\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_video\":\"\"}', 4, 3, '', '', 1, 0, '{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\"}', 0, '*', ''),
(23, 132, 'Anesthesia Needle', 'dental-anesthesia-needle', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">The anesthesia needle is a slender, hollow instrument used in medical procedures to deliver local anesthesia with precision and minimal discomfort. Featuring a sharp, beveled tip for smooth insertion, it ensures accurate delivery of the anesthetic solution to the targeted area. With its ultra-thin gauge and high-quality construction, it minimizes tissue trauma and patient discomfort during administration. Equipped with a hub for secure attachment to a syringe, it facilitates easy aspiration and injection of the anesthetic agent. Trusted by healthcare professionals worldwide, the anesthesia needle plays a crucial role in ensuring patient comfort and pain management during various medical and dental procedures. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Also known as a dental syringe or local anesthetic syringe, is a crucial instrument in dentistry used for delivering local anesthesia to numb specific areas of the mouth during dental procedures. It typically consists of a stainless steel needle attached to a plastic or metal syringe barrel, allowing precise control and administration of the anesthetic solution. Dental professionals rely on anesthesia needles to provide pain relief and ensure patient comfort during various dental treatments, including fillings, extractions, root canals, and periodontal procedures. The anesthesia needle is designed to penetrate the soft tissues of the oral mucosa, allowing the anesthetic solution to be deposited near the nerves responsible for sensation in the targeted area.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">The design of anesthesia needles varies depending on factors such as gauge size, length, and bevel configuration, which can influence the speed and depth of anesthesia delivery. Common types of anesthesia needles include short needles for infiltrative anesthesia and long needles for nerve block anesthesia. Dental practitioners carefully select the appropriate needle and technique based on the specific procedure being performed and the patient\'s individual needs. Prior to administration, dental professionals often use topical anesthetic gel or spray to numb the injection site and minimize discomfort during needle insertion.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Despite advancements in dental technology and the availability of alternative anesthesia delivery methods, such as electronic anesthesia devices and needle-free systems, the anesthesia needle remains a widely used and effective tool in dentistry. Its simplicity, reliability, and cost-effectiveness make it a preferred choice for many dental procedures. Dental professionals adhere to strict infection control protocols when handling anesthesia needles, ensuring proper sterilization and disposal to prevent the transmission of infectious agents between patients. Overall, the anesthesia needle plays a vital role in modern dental practice, enabling clinicians to deliver safe and effective pain management solutions to enhance patient comfort and facilitate successful treatment outcomes.</span></p>', '', 1, 8, '2024-05-04 06:31:51', 748, '', '2024-05-24 02:55:47', 748, NULL, NULL, '2024-05-04 06:31:51', NULL, '{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}', '{\"urla\":\"\",\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":\"\",\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":\"\",\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}', '{\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"info_block_show_title\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_page_title\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_image\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_image_alt_txt\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_article_format\":\"standard\",\"helix_ultimate_audio\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_gallery\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_video\":\"\"}', 6, 2, '', '', 1, 0, '{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\"}', 0, '*', ''),
(24, 133, 'Saliva Ejector Dental', 'saliva-ejector-dental', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\">The saliva ejector, an essential tool in dental practice, efficiently removes excess saliva and fluids from the oral cavity during procedures. With its flexible and non-irritating design, it ensures patient comfort throughout treatment. This device aids in maintaining a clear field of view for the dentist, enhancing precision and efficiency during dental procedures. By effectively managing saliva and moisture, the saliva ejector contributes to a cleaner and more hygienic environment, reducing the risk of contamination and enhancing patient safety. Trust in the reliability and effectiveness of the saliva ejector for optimal dental care outcomes. D</span><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">esigned to remove saliva, water, blood, and debris from the patient\'s mouth during dental procedures. It consists of a slender, flexible tube connected to a vacuum system, which generates suction to aspirate fluids from the oral cavity. Dental professionals rely on saliva ejectors to maintain a dry and clear field of view, enhancing visibility and facilitating efficient treatment delivery. The saliva ejector is typically positioned near the patient\'s cheek or tongue to capture fluids and prevent aspiration during procedures.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">During routine dental treatments such as cleanings, fillings, and extractions, saliva ejectors play a vital role in improving patient comfort and safety. By continuously removing excess moisture and debris, saliva ejectors help prevent gag reflexes and ensure a more pleasant experience for the patient. Moreover, the elimination of saliva and blood from the treatment area enhances the accuracy of dental procedures and reduces the risk of contamination, promoting optimal treatment outcomes. Dental professionals often utilize saliva ejectors in conjunction with other suction devices, such as high-volume evacuators, to maintain a clean and controlled working environment.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">In addition to their clinical utility, saliva ejectors contribute to infection control in dental settings by minimizing the spread of microorganisms and aerosols. The continuous suction provided by saliva ejectors helps capture and contain airborne particles generated during dental procedures, reducing the risk of cross-contamination between patients and dental staff. Dental practices adhere to strict sterilization protocols for saliva ejectors, ensuring that they are properly cleaned, disinfected, and disposed of after each use to prevent the transmission of infectious agents. Overall, saliva ejectors are indispensable tools in dental practice, promoting patient comfort, safety, and infection prevention while facilitating efficient and effective treatment delivery. In modern dentistry, saliva ejectors come in various designs and sizes to accommodate different patient needs and treatment requirements. Some saliva ejectors feature disposable tips for single-use applications, offering convenience and hygiene benefits by eliminating the need for sterilization between patients. Dental professionals often customize the positioning of saliva ejectors based on the specific procedure being performed and the patient\'s anatomy, ensuring optimal suction and comfort throughout the treatment. Additionally, advancements in suction technology continue to improve the efficiency and performance of saliva ejectors, enhancing their effectiveness in maintaining a clean and dry oral environment during dental procedures. As an integral part of dental practice, saliva ejectors contribute to the overall quality of patient care by supporting a safe, comfortable, and hygienic treatment experience.</span></p>', '', 1, 8, '2024-05-04 06:33:22', 748, '', '2024-05-24 02:53:41', 748, NULL, NULL, '2024-05-04 06:33:22', NULL, '{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}', '{\"urla\":\"\",\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":\"\",\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":\"\",\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}', '{\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"info_block_show_title\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_page_title\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_image\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_image_alt_txt\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_article_format\":\"standard\",\"helix_ultimate_audio\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_gallery\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_video\":\"\"}', 7, 1, '', '', 1, 1, '{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\"}', 0, '*', ''),
(25, 134, 'Dental Prophy Brush', 'dental-prophy-brush', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Dental prophy brushes are essential tools in oral hygiene maintenance, designed to efficiently remove plaque, stains, and debris from tooth surfaces and interdental areas. These small, disposable brushes feature soft bristles attached to a flexible plastic or rubber handle, making them gentle yet effective for cleaning around teeth and dental restorations. Dental prophy brushes come in various shapes, sizes, and textures to accommodate different patient needs and preferences, ensuring thorough cleaning and polishing of the teeth. Dental professionals commonly use prophy brushes during prophylaxis appointments, where they are employed in conjunction with prophylaxis paste to achieve a smooth and polished finish on the tooth surfaces.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">During a dental prophylaxis procedure, the dental hygienist or dentist selects an appropriate prophy brush based on the patient\'s oral health status and the areas requiring cleaning. The brush is then dipped into prophylaxis paste, which contains abrasive particles to help remove surface stains and plaque. With gentle pressure and circular motions, the prophy brush is used to clean the outer surfaces of the teeth, paying particular attention to hard-to-reach areas and interdental spaces. Dental prophy brushes are also effective for cleaning along the gumline, where plaque and debris can accumulate and contribute to gum disease if not removed regularly.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">In addition to their use in professional dental cleanings, dental prophy brushes are often recommended for home oral care as part of a comprehensive dental hygiene routine. Patients can use prophy brushes to supplement their regular toothbrushing and flossing routine, providing extra cleaning power for hard-to-reach areas between teeth and around dental appliances like braces or bridges. With proper technique and regular use, dental prophy brushes can help maintain optimal oral hygiene, reduce the risk of cavities and gum disease, and promote a healthy and radiant smile. Dental prophy brushes are particularly beneficial for patients with orthodontic appliances, as they can effectively clean around brackets, wires, and bands, where plaque accumulation is common. Furthermore, the gentle bristles of prophy brushes make them suitable for patients with sensitive gums or dental restorations, ensuring thorough cleaning without causing discomfort or damage. Some prophy brushes feature specialized designs, such as tapered or angled bristles, to facilitate access to difficult-to-reach areas and ensure comprehensive plaque removal. Dental professionals often recommend regular use of prophy brushes as part of a personalized preventive care plan to help patients maintain optimal oral health between dental visits. Additionally, disposable prophy brushes offer convenience and hygiene benefits, as they can be safely discarded after each use, minimizing the risk of cross-contamination and promoting infection control in dental settings.</span></p>', '', 1, 8, '2024-05-04 06:35:22', 748, '', '2024-05-24 05:26:34', 748, NULL, NULL, '2024-05-04 06:35:22', NULL, '{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}', '{\"urla\":\"\",\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":\"\",\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":\"\",\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}', '{\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"info_block_show_title\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_page_title\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_image\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_image_alt_txt\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_article_format\":\"standard\",\"helix_ultimate_audio\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_gallery\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_video\":\"\"}', 14, 0, '', '', 1, 0, '{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\"}', 0, '*', '');
