(7, 'index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=2', 'index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=2:tm033-silicone-impression-material&catid=9', 'Silicone Impression', ' Silicone impression material stands as a cornerstone in modern dentistry, renowned for its versatility, accuracy, and reliability in capturing detailed impressions of the oral cavity. Composed of silicone polymers, these impression materials come in various viscosities and set times to accommodate different clinical scenarios. The silicone impression material is commonly used in both fixed and removable prosthodontics, orthodontics, and implant dentistry due to its ability to accurately replicate tooth morphology and soft tissue contours. Its hydrophobic nature ensures excellent moisture control, making it ideal for capturing precise impressions even in challenging clinical conditions. It dispensed from cartridges and mixed using an automixing system to ensure uniformity and consistency of the material. Once injected into the impression tray, it flows smoothly and evenly over the teeth and soft tissues, capturing minute details with exceptional clarity. Dental professionals appreciate silicone impressions for their dimensional stability, which prevents distortion over time and ensures accurate reproduction of the oral structures. Moreover, the elasticity of silicone impression material allows for easy removal from the mouth without tearing or distortion, contributing to a comfortable experience for the patient. Silicone impressions offer clinicians the flexibility to choose from a range of materials tailored to specific clinical needs, including light-bodied, medium-bodied, and heavy-bodied consistencies. Light-bodied silicone is typically used for syringeable precision around the margins of preparations, while heavy-bodied silicone provides adequate bulk and support for full-arch impressions. Additionally, the advent of addition-cured silicone materials has further enhanced the accuracy and reliability of impressions, ensuring optimal fit and longevity of dental restorations. With its exceptional performance and versatility, silicone impression material continues to play a pivotal role in achieving predictable and esthetic outcomes in contemporary dental practice. Silicone impression materials are favored by dental professionals for their excellent tear strength, which ensures the integrity of the impression during removal and subsequent handling. The ability of silicone impressions to capture fine details, such as surface texture and margin delineation, facilitates precise restorative work and contributes to the longevity of dental restorations. Furthermore, silicone impression materials exhibit minimal distortion upon removal from the mouth, allowing for accurate reproduction of the patient\'s oral anatomy. This dimensional stability is particularly advantageous when fabricating indirect restorations, such as crowns and bridges, where precision is paramount for optimal fit and function. Additionally, silicone impressions can be used in conjunction with various tray types, including stock trays, custom trays, and dual-arch trays, providing flexibility in impression-taking techniques to suit individual patient needs and preferences. ', '2024-05-24 02:41:27', 'dd932955d3857d1c1017bd9218b6ab67', 1, 1, 1, '*', '2024-05-03 23:28:02', NULL, '2024-05-03 23:28:02', NULL, 0, 0, 3, ),
