(17, 'index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=11', 'index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=11:tissue-dispessor&catid=10', 'Tissue Dispessor', ' A tissue dispenser is an essential accessory in dental and medical settings, designed to provide convenient access to disposable tissues for various clinical purposes. Typically constructed from durable materials such as plastic or stainless steel, tissue dispensers are sturdy and easy to clean, ensuring hygienic usage. They are often wall-mounted or placed on countertops for easy accessibility during patient care. With their practical design, tissue dispensers help maintain a clean and organized clinical environment, promoting efficiency and professionalism. Available in various sizes and styles, tissue dispensers offer flexibility to suit the specific needs and preferences of different healthcare facilities. It appears there might be a misunderstanding regarding the term \"tissue dispissor\" as it doesn\'t seem to correspond to a recognized dental instrument. However, I can provide information on tissue dispensers, which are commonly used in dental offices for various purposes. Tissue dispensers are essential accessories in dental offices, providing patients and dental professionals with convenient access to tissues for a wide range of clinical and personal uses. These dispensers typically consist of a container or box designed to hold a stack of disposable tissues, with a mechanism for easy retrieval and dispensing. Tissue dispensers are strategically placed throughout the dental office in areas such as patient treatment rooms, waiting areas, and restroom facilities to ensure that tissues are readily available when needed. In clinical settings, tissue dispensers serve multiple purposes, including wiping excess saliva, water, or dental materials from the face and hands during dental procedures, providing comfort to patients during treatment, and maintaining cleanliness and hygiene in the dental operatory. Dental