(20, 'index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=14', 'index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=14:portable-x-ray&catid=10', 'Portable X-ray ', ' A portable X-Ray machine is a compact and versatile tool used in dental settings to capture detailed images of patients\' teeth and jawbones. Designed for mobility and convenience, it allows dental professionals to perform X-Ray examinations directly in the treatment room or even in remote locations. Equipped with advanced technology, such as digital sensors and wireless connectivity, portable X-Ray machines produce high-quality images with minimal radiation exposure to patients. Their lightweight and ergonomic design enable easy maneuverability, enhancing workflow efficiency and patient comfort. Portable X-Ray machines are indispensable assets in dental practices, enabling accurate diagnosis and treatment planning with flexibility and precision Also known as handheld X-ray devices or portable radiography units, are compact and lightweight imaging systems used in dental practice to capture diagnostic X-ray images with flexibility and convenience. These portable units provide dental professionals with the ability to obtain intraoral and extraoral radiographs directly at the patient\'s chairside, eliminating the need for patients to visit a separate radiography room. Portable X-ray machines typically consist of a handheld X-ray generator connected to a control panel and a digital sensor or film holder. These devices are powered by rechargeable batteries or electrical outlets, allowing for easy transport and use in various clinical settings. One of the primary advantages of portable X-ray machines is their versatility and mobility, enabling dental practitioners to perform diagnostic imaging procedures efficiently and effectively in diverse environments, such as hospital dental clinics, nursing homes, or mobile dental facilities. These devices offer flexibility in positioning and angulation, allowing dental professionals to capture high-quality radiographic images while accommodating patients of different ages and physical conditions. Portable X-ray machines are particularly useful for capturing emergency radiographs or imaging patients with limited mobility who may have difficulty accessing traditional X-ray units. In addition to their convenience and mobility, portable X-ray machines utilize digital imaging technology, allowing for the immediate acquisition and viewing of radiographic images on a computer screen or handheld device. This digital workflow enhances diagnostic efficiency by enabling real-time image interpretation and facilitating communication between dental professionals and patients. Furthermore, digital radiography offers advantages such as reduced radiation exposure, enhanced image quality, and improved storage and retrieval of patient records compared to traditional film-based radiography. With the increasing adoption of digital imaging technology in dentistry, portable X-ray machines continue to play a crucial role in delivering high-quality diagnostic imaging services while improving patient comfort and safety. ', '2024-05-24 03:06:56', '0a7b49569123cc767b0f6afce1b82abe', 1, 1, 1, '*', '2024-05-04 05:24:22', NULL, '2024-05-04 05:24:22', NULL, 0, 0, 3, );
