(86, 'com_content.article.4', '', '2024-05-24 02:30:43', 748, 3937, 'bdbf517f82cae86eedb5ce84d280fc010886ac2d', '{\"id\":\"4\",\"asset_id\":113,\"title\":\"Glass Ionomer Cement\",\"alias\":\"glass-ionomer-cement\",\"introtext\":\"<p><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Glass Ionomer Cement (GIC) stands as a cornerstone in modern restorative dentistry, prized for its versatility and efficacy in a myriad of clinical applications. Comprising a unique blend of powdered glass and a liquid containing an acidic solution, this dental material undergoes a chemical reaction upon mixing, resulting in the formation of a hardened material known as the glass ionomer. This exceptional bonding mechanism allows GIC to adhere securely to tooth structure, ensuring excellent retention and sealing properties, which are vital for the success and longevity of dental restorations.\\u00a0<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">One of the standout features of GIC is its ability to gradually release fluoride ions over time. This release of fluoride not only helps in the prevention of secondary caries but also aids in the strengthening of adjacent tooth structure, making it an invaluable asset in pediatric dentistry and for patients at heightened risk of dental decay. Moreover, GIC exhibits a coefficient of thermal expansion comparable to that of natural tooth structure, minimizing the risk of marginal leakage and secondary decay, thus ensuring the long-term stability of restorations.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Despite its exceptional attributes, it\'s important to note that GIC does have limitations, particularly in terms of mechanical properties when compared to composite resins. As such, its use may be restricted in high-load-bearing areas. Nevertheless, its ease of use, natural appearance, and fluoride-releasing capabilities make it a preferred choice for a wide range of restorative procedures. From filling cavities to cementing crowns and bridges, Glass Ionomer Cement continues to be a trusted companion for dental professionals worldwide, delivering reliable and aesthetically pleasing results while contributing to improved oral health outcomes for patients.<\\/span><\\/p>\",\"fulltext\":\"\",\"state\":\"1\",\"catid\":9,\"created\":\"2024-05-04 03:57:12\",\"created_by\":\"748\",\"created_by_alias\":\"\",\"modified\":\"2024-05-24 02:30:43\",\"modified_by\":748,\"checked_out\":748,\"checked_out_time\":\"2024-05-24 02:29:21\",\"publish_up\":\"2024-05-04 03:57:12\",\"publish_down\":null,\"images\":\"{\\\"image_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_caption\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_caption\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"urls\":\"{\\\"urla\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlatext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targeta\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlbtext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlc\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlctext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetc\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"attribs\":\"{\\\"article_layout\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_titles\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_tags\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"info_block_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"info_block_show_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_create_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_modify_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publish_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_item_navigation\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_hits\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_noauth\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urls_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"alternative_readmore\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"article_page_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publishing_options\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_article_opt