(91, 'com_content.article.3', '', '2024-05-24 02:38:37', 748, 4842, '0f595c8281fd6653f89f8e22560c4ce331801932', '{\"id\":\"3\",\"asset_id\":112,\"title\":\"Alginate Impression\",\"alias\":\"alginate-impression\",\"introtext\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Alginate impression material is a staple in dentistry, known for its versatility and ease of use. It consists primarily of sodium alginate derived from seaweed, making it biocompatible and safe for intraoral use. When mixed with water, alginate powder forms a viscous paste that can accurately capture the intricate details of a patient\'s teeth and surrounding oral structures. Dental professionals rely on alginate impressions for various purposes, including fabricating custom dental appliances such as crowns, bridges, and dentures. It\\u00a0is a widely-used dental material employed for capturing detailed impressions of a patient\'s teeth and surrounding oral structures. Composed primarily of sodium alginate derived from seaweed, it exhibits excellent compatibility with oral tissues and offers a safe and non-toxic option for dental procedures.\\u00a0<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">alginate powder is mixed with water to form a viscous paste that quickly sets into a rubbery consistency when placed in the mouth. Dental professionals rely on alginate impressions for various purposes, including fabricating custom dental appliances like crowns, bridges, and dentures. Its ability to accurately reproduce intricate details of the oral cavity makes it indispensable in the field of prosthodontics and orthodontics.It is<\\/span><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">\\u00a0low cost compared to other impression materials, making them accessible for a wide range of patients. Despite its advantages, alginate does have limitations, such as its tendency to shrink slightly upon setting and its relatively short working time. Nonetheless, with proper technique and handling, alginate impression remains a staple in dental practices worldwide, serving as a fundamental tool in delivering quality oral healthcare.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Alginate Impressions is relatively short, typically ranging from one to four minutes, depending on the specific formulation and environmental conditions. This quick setting time allows for efficient and comfortable impression-taking procedures for patients. However, it\'s essential for dental practitioners to work swiftly and precisely to ensure optimal results and avoid distortion of the impression. Despite its advantages, alginate impressions do have limitations, such as susceptibility to dimensional changes over time and a relatively short shelf life once mixed. Nonetheless, with proper technique and handling, alginate impression material remains an invaluable tool in modern dentistry, facilitating accurate diagnoses and the creation of high-quality dental restorations to improve patients\' oral health and aesthetics.<\\/span><\\/p>\",\"fulltext\":\"\",\"state\":\"1\",\"catid\":9,\"created\":\"2024-05-04 02:59:36\",\"created_by\":\"748\",\"created_by_alias\":\"\",\"modified\":\"2024-05-24 02:38:37\",\"modified_by\":748,\"checked_out\":748,\"checked_out_time\":\"2024-05-24 02:35:57\",\"publish_up\":\"2024-05-04 02:59:36\",\"publish_down\":null,\"images\":\"{\\\"image_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_caption\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_caption\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"urls\":\"{\\\"urla\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlatext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targeta\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlb\\\":\\\