(99, 'com_content.article.5', '', '2024-05-24 02:49:24', 748, 5137, '897a2c5643de2744c9a9f0a23e509f4706d9b1ed', '{\"id\":\"5\",\"asset_id\":114,\"title\":\"Dental Amalgam\",\"alias\":\"dental-amalgam\",\"introtext\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Dental amalgam is a commonly used dental filling material composed of a mixture of metals, including silver, tin, copper, and mercury. It has been utilized in dentistry for over a century due to its durability, strength, and affordability. Dental amalgam is known for its silver-gray appearance and ability to withstand the forces of chewing, making it suitable for restoring posterior teeth subjected to high occlusal forces. Despite concerns about mercury content, dental amalgam is considered safe for use in dental restorations when properly handled and placed according to established protocols. However, due to aesthetic considerations and the availability of alternative materials, such as composite resin, the use of dental amalgam has declined in recent years.\\u00a0<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">It has long been a cornerstone of restorative dentistry, valued for its durability, strength, and affordability. Composed primarily of a mixture of silver, tin, copper, and mercury, dental amalgam has been used for over a century to fill cavities and restore damaged teeth. The high content of silver in dental amalgam contributes to its excellent strength and wear resistance, making it particularly suitable for restoring posterior teeth subjected to heavy chewing forces. Additionally, the inclusion of copper in the amalgam alloy enhances its corrosion resistance and durability, ensuring long-term stability of the restoration.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">The process of placing dental amalgam involves mixing the powdered alloy with liquid mercury to form a plastic mass that can be packed into the prepared cavity. Once placed, the amalgam undergoes a chemical reaction known as amalgamation, in which the mercury reacts with the other metals to form a strong, solid restoration. Dental professionals appreciate the ease of handling and manipulation of dental amalgam, as it allows for efficient placement and contouring of the restoration to achieve optimal occlusion and aesthetics. Moreover, dental amalgam exhibits a relatively low coefficient of thermal expansion, minimizing the risk of marginal leakage and secondary decay over time.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Despite its longstanding history and proven clinical performance, dental amalgam has faced scrutiny in recent years due to concerns about its mercury content and environmental impact. However, numerous studies and regulatory agencies, including the American Dental Association (ADA) and the World Health Organization (WHO), have affirmed the safety and efficacy of dental amalgam when used according to established guidelines. Dental amalgam remains a valuable treatment option, particularly in situations where durability and longevity are paramount, such as in patients with high caries risk or those requiring extensive restorations. While alternative materials like composite resins continue to gain popularity, dental amalgam continues to be a trusted and reliable choice for restoring teeth and preserving oral health.<\\/span><\\/p>\",\"fulltext\":\"\",\"state\":\"1\",\"catid\":9,\"created\":\"2024-05-04 04:09:22\",\"created_by\":\"748\",\"created_by_alias\":\"\",\"modified\":\"2024-05-24 02:49:24\",\"modified_by\":748,\"checked_out\":748,\"checked_out_time\":\"2024-05-24 02:49:03\",\"publish_up\":\"2024-05-04 04:09:22\",\"publish_down\":null,\"images\":\"{\\\"image_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_caption\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_caption\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"urls\":\"{\\\"urla\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlatext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targeta\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlbtext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlc\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlctext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetc\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"attribs\":\"{\\\"article_layout\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_titles\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_tags\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"info_block_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"info_block_show_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_create_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_modify_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publish_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_item_navigation\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_hits\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_noauth\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urls_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"alternative_readmore\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"article_page_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publishing_options\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_article_options\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_urls_images_backend\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_urls_images_frontend\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_image\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_image_alt_txt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_article_format\\\":\\\"standard\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_audio\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_gallery\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_video\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"version\":6,\"ordering\":4,\"metakey\":\"\",\"metadesc\":\"\",\"access\":1,\"hits\":0,\"metadata\":\"{\\\"robots\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"rights\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"featured\":\"0\",\"language\":\"*\",\"note\":\"\"}', 0),
(100, 'com_content.article.25', '', '2024-05-24 02:50:45', 748, 4177, '0b9a6921ca49cd4a121f01d9b23b73a14a88ada1', '{\"id\":\"25\",\"asset_id\":134,\"title\":\"Dental Prophy Brush\",\"alias\":\"dental-prophy-brush\",\"introtext\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Dental prophy brushes are essential tools in oral hygiene maintenance, designed to efficiently remove plaque, stains, and debris from tooth surfaces and interdental areas. These small, disposable brushes feature soft bristles attached to a flexible plastic or rubber handle, making them gentle yet effective for cleaning around teeth and dental restorations. Dental prophy brushes come in various shapes, sizes, and textures to accommodate different patient needs and preferences, ensuring thorough cleaning and polishing of the teeth. Dental professionals commonly use prophy brushes during prophylaxis appointments, where they are employed in conjunction with prophylaxis paste to achieve a smooth and polished finish on the tooth surfaces.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">During a dental prophylaxis procedure, the dental hygienist or dentist selects an appropriate prophy brush based on the patient\'s oral health status and the areas requiring cleaning. The brush is then dipped into prophylaxis paste, which contains abrasive particles to help remove surface stains and plaque. With gentle pressure and circular motions, the prophy brush is used to clean the outer surfaces of the teeth, paying particular attention to hard-to-reach areas and interdental spaces. Dental prophy brushes are also effective for cleaning along the gumline, where plaque and debris can accumulate and contribute to gum disease if not removed regularly.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">In addition to their use in professional dental cleanings, dental prophy brushes are often recommended for home oral care as part of a comprehensive dental hygiene routine. Patients can use prophy brushes to supplement their regular toothbrushing and flossing routine, providing extra cleaning power for hard-to-reach areas between teeth and around dental appliances like braces or bridges. With proper technique and regular use, dental prophy brushes can help maintain optimal oral hygiene, reduce the risk of cavities and gum disease, and promote a healthy and radiant smile.<\\/span><\\/p>\",\"fulltext\":\"\",\"state\":\"1\",\"catid\":8,\"created\":\"2024-05-04 06:35:22\",\"created_by\":\"748\",\"created_by_alias\":\"\",\"modified\":\"2024-05-24 02:50:45\",\"modified_by\":748,\"checked_out\":748,\"checked_out_time\":\"2024-05-24 02:50:29\",\"publish_up\":\"2024-05-04 06:35:22\",\"publish_down\":null,\"images\":\"{\\\"image_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_caption\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_caption\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"urls\":\"{\\\"urla\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlatext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targeta\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlbtext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlc\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlctext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetc\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"attribs\":\"{\\\"article_layout\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_titles\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_tags\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"info_block_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"info_block_show_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_create_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_modify_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publish_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_item_navigation\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_hits\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_noauth\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urls_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"alternative_readmore\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"article_page_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publishing_options\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_article_options\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_urls_images_backend\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_urls_images_frontend\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_image\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_image_alt_txt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_article_format\\\":\\\"standard\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_audio\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_gallery\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_video\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"version\":11,\"ordering\":0,\"metakey\":\"\",\"metadesc\":\"\",\"access\":1,\"hits\":0,\"metadata\":\"{\\\"robots\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"rights\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"featured\":\"0\",\"language\":\"*\",\"note\":\"\"}', 0),
(101, 'com_content.article.25', '', '2024-05-24 02:51:31', 748, 5144, 'a17db0e62d6999913f01f432bea3a296fb913d4b', '{\"id\":\"25\",\"asset_id\":134,\"title\":\"Dental Prophy Brush\",\"alias\":\"dental-prophy-brush\",\"introtext\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Dental prophy brushes are essential tools in oral hygiene maintenance, designed to efficiently remove plaque, stains, and debris from tooth surfaces and interdental areas. These small, disposable brushes feature soft bristles attached to a flexible plastic or rubber handle, making them gentle yet effective for cleaning around teeth and dental restorations. Dental prophy brushes come in various shapes, sizes, and textures to accommodate different patient needs and preferences, ensuring thorough cleaning and polishing of the teeth. Dental professionals commonly use prophy brushes during prophylaxis appointments, where they are employed in conjunction with prophylaxis paste to achieve a smooth and polished finish on the tooth surfaces.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">During a dental prophylaxis procedure, the dental hygienist or dentist selects an appropriate prophy brush based on the patient\'s oral health status and the areas requiring cleaning. The brush is then dipped into prophylaxis paste, which contains abrasive particles to help remove surface stains and plaque. With gentle pressure and circular motions, the prophy brush is used to clean the outer surfaces of the teeth, paying particular attention to hard-to-reach areas and interdental spaces. Dental prophy brushes are also effective for cleaning along the gumline, where plaque and debris can accumulate and contribute to gum disease if not removed regularly.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">In addition to their use in professional dental cleanings, dental prophy brushes are often recommended for home oral care as part of a comprehensive dental hygiene routine. Patients can use prophy brushes to supplement their regular toothbrushing and flossing routine, providing extra cleaning power for hard-to-reach areas between teeth and around dental appliances like braces or bridges. With proper technique and regular use, dental prophy brushes can help maintain optimal oral hygiene, reduce the risk of cavities and gum disease, and promote a healthy and radiant smile. Dental prophy brushes are particularly beneficial for patients with orthodontic appliances, as they can effectively clean around brackets, wires, and bands, where plaque accumulation is common. Furthermore, the gentle bristles of prophy brushes make them suitable for patients with sensitive gums or dental restorations, ensuring thorough cleaning without causing discomfort or damage. Some prophy brushes feature specialized designs, such as tapered or angled bristles, to facilitate access to difficult-to-reach areas and ensure comprehensive plaque removal. Dental professionals often recommend regular use of prophy brushes as part of a personalized preventive care plan to help patients maintain optimal oral health between dental visits. Additionally, disposable prophy brushes offer convenience and hygiene benefits, as they can be safely discarded after each use, minimizing the risk of cross-contamination and promoting infection control in dental settings.<\\/span><\\/p>\",\"fulltext\":\"\",\"state\":\"1\",\"catid\":8,\"created\":\"2024-05-04 06:35:22\",\"created_by\":\"748\",\"created_by_alias\":\"\",\"modified\":\"2024-05-24 02:51:31\",\"modified_by\":748,\"checked_out\":748,\"checked_out_time\":\"2024-05-24 02:50:45\",\"publish_up\":\"2024-05-04 06:35:22\",\"publish_down\":null,\"images\":\"{\\\"image_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_caption\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_caption\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"urls\":\"{\\\"urla\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlatext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targeta\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlbtext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlc\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlctext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetc\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"attribs\":\"{\\\"article_layout\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_titles\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_tags\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"info_block_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"info_block_show_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_create_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_modify_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publish_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_item_navigation\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_hits\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_noauth\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urls_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"alternative_readmore\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"article_page_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publishing_options\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_article_options\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_urls_images_backend\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_urls_images_frontend\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_image\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_image_alt_txt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_article_format\\\":\\\"standard\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_audio\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_gallery\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_video\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"version\":12,\"ordering\":0,\"metakey\":\"\",\"metadesc\":\"\",\"access\":1,\"hits\":0,\"metadata\":\"{\\\"robots\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"rights\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"featured\":\"0\",\"language\":\"*\",\"note\":\"\"}', 0),
(102, 'com_content.article.24', '', '2024-05-24 02:52:46', 748, 4827, 'd6cc63c82227e68b2714a5c5247583d2c4c9bef1', '{\"id\":\"24\",\"asset_id\":133,\"title\":\"Saliva Ejector Dental\",\"alias\":\"saliva-ejector-dental\",\"introtext\":\"<p><span style=\\\"font-size: 14px; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\\\">The saliva ejector, an essential tool in dental practice, efficiently removes excess saliva and fluids from the oral cavity during procedures. With its flexible and non-irritating design, it ensures patient comfort throughout treatment. This device aids in maintaining a clear field of view for the dentist, enhancing precision and efficiency during dental procedures. By effectively managing saliva and moisture, the saliva ejector contributes to a cleaner and more hygienic environment, reducing the risk of contamination and enhancing patient safety. Trust in the reliability and effectiveness of the saliva ejector for optimal dental care outcomes. D<\\/span><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">esigned to remove saliva, water, blood, and debris from the patient\'s mouth during dental procedures. It consists of a slender, flexible tube connected to a vacuum system, which generates suction to aspirate fluids from the oral cavity. Dental professionals rely on saliva ejectors to maintain a dry and clear field of view, enhancing visibility and facilitating efficient treatment delivery. The saliva ejector is typically positioned near the patient\'s cheek or tongue to capture fluids and prevent aspiration during procedures.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">During routine dental treatments such as cleanings, fillings, and extractions, saliva ejectors play a vital role in improving patient comfort and safety. By continuously removing excess moisture and debris, saliva ejectors help prevent gag reflexes and ensure a more pleasant experience for the patient. Moreover, the elimination of saliva and blood from the treatment area enhances the accuracy of dental procedures and reduces the risk of contamination, promoting optimal treatment outcomes. Dental professionals often utilize saliva ejectors in conjunction with other suction devices, such as high-volume evacuators, to maintain a clean and controlled working environment.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">In addition to their clinical utility, saliva ejectors contribute to infection control in dental settings by minimizing the spread of microorganisms and aerosols. The continuous suction provided by saliva ejectors helps capture and contain airborne particles generated during dental procedures, reducing the risk of cross-contamination between patients and dental staff. Dental practices adhere to strict sterilization protocols for saliva ejectors, ensuring that they are properly cleaned, disinfected, and disposed of after each use to prevent the transmission of infectious agents. Overall, saliva ejectors are indispensable tools in dental practice, promoting patient comfort, safety, and infection prevention while facilitating efficient and effective treatment delivery.<\\/span><\\/p>\",\"fulltext\":\"\",\"state\":\"1\",\"catid\":8,\"created\":\"2024-05-04 06:33:22\",\"created_by\":\"748\",\"created_by_alias\":\"\",\"modified\":\"2024-05-24 02:52:46\",\"modified_by\":748,\"checked_out\":748,\"checked_out_time\":\"2024-05-24 02:52:21\",\"publish_up\":\"2024-05-04 06:33:22\",\"publish_down\":null,\"images\":\"{\\\"image_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_caption\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_caption\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"urls\":\"{\\\"urla\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlatext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targeta\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlbtext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlc\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlctext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetc\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"attribs\":\"{\\\"article_layout\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_titles\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_tags\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"info_block_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"info_block_show_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_create_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_modify_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publish_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_item_navigation\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_hits\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_noauth\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urls_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"alternative_readmore\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"article_page_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publishing_options\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_article_options\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_urls_images_backend\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_urls_images_frontend\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_image\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_image_alt_txt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_article_format\\\":\\\"standard\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_audio\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_gallery\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_video\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"version\":5,\"ordering\":1,\"metakey\":\"\",\"metadesc\":\"\",\"access\":1,\"hits\":1,\"metadata\":\"{\\\"robots\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"rights\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"featured\":\"0\",\"language\":\"*\",\"note\":\"\"}', 0),
(103, 'com_content.article.24', '', '2024-05-24 02:53:25', 748, 5751, '4bfe70e517d6879bd3f10417c82dca06478564a4', '{\"id\":\"24\",\"asset_id\":133,\"title\":\"Saliva Ejector Dental\",\"alias\":\"saliva-ejector-dental\",\"introtext\":\"<p><span style=\\\"font-size: 14px; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\\\">The saliva ejector, an essential tool in dental practice, efficiently removes excess saliva and fluids from the oral cavity during procedures. With its flexible and non-irritating design, it ensures patient comfort throughout treatment. This device aids in maintaining a clear field of view for the dentist, enhancing precision and efficiency during dental procedures. By effectively managing saliva and moisture, the saliva ejector contributes to a cleaner and more hygienic environment, reducing the risk of contamination and enhancing patient safety. Trust in the reliability and effectiveness of the saliva ejector for optimal dental care outcomes. D<\\/span><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">esigned to remove saliva, water, blood, and debris from the patient\'s mouth during dental procedures. It consists of a slender, flexible tube connected to a vacuum system, which generates suction to aspirate fluids from the oral cavity. Dental professionals rely on saliva ejectors to maintain a dry and clear field of view, enhancing visibility and facilitating efficient treatment delivery. The saliva ejector is typically positioned near the patient\'s cheek or tongue to capture fluids and prevent aspiration during procedures.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">During routine dental treatments such as cleanings, fillings, and extractions, saliva ejectors play a vital role in improving patient comfort and safety. By continuously removing excess moisture and debris, saliva ejectors help prevent gag reflexes and ensure a more pleasant experience for the patient. Moreover, the elimination of saliva and blood from the treatment area enhances the accuracy of dental procedures and reduces the risk of contamination, promoting optimal treatment outcomes. Dental professionals often utilize saliva ejectors in conjunction with other suction devices, such as high-volume evacuators, to maintain a clean and controlled working environment.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">In addition to their clinical utility, saliva ejectors contribute to infection control in dental settings by minimizing the spread of microorganisms and aerosols. The continuous suction provided by saliva ejectors helps capture and contain airborne particles generated during dental procedures, reducing the risk of cross-contamination between patients and dental staff. Dental practices adhere to strict sterilization protocols for saliva ejectors, ensuring that they are properly cleaned, disinfected, and disposed of after each use to prevent the transmission of infectious agents. Overall, saliva ejectors are indispensable tools in dental practice, promoting patient comfort, safety, and infection prevention while facilitating efficient and effective treatment delivery. In modern dentistry, saliva ejectors come in various designs and sizes to accommodate different patient needs and treatment requirements. Some saliva ejectors feature disposable tips for single-use applications, offering convenience and hygiene benefits by eliminating the need for sterilization between patients. Dental professionals often customize the positioning of saliva ejectors based on the specific procedure being performed and the patient\'s anatomy, ensuring optimal suction and comfort throughout the treatment. Additionally, advancements in suction technology continue to improve the efficiency and performance of saliva ejectors, enhancing their effectiveness in maintaining a clean and dry oral environment during dental procedures. As an integral part of dental practice, saliva ejectors contribute to the overall quality of patient care by supporting a safe, comfortable, and hygienic treatment experience.<\\/span><\\/p>\",\"fulltext\":\"\",\"state\":\"1\",\"catid\":8,\"created\":\"2024-05-04 06:33:22\",\"created_by\":\"748\",\"created_by_alias\":\"\",\"modified\":\"2024-05-24 02:53:25\",\"modified_by\":748,\"checked_out\":748,\"checked_out_time\":\"2024-05-24 02:52:55\",\"publish_up\":\"2024-05-04 06:33:22\",\"publish_down\":null,\"images\":\"{\\\"image_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_caption\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_caption\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"urls\":\"{\\\"urla\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlatext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targeta\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlbtext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlc\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlctext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetc\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"attribs\":\"{\\\"article_layout\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_titles\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_tags\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"info_block_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"info_block_show_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_create_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_modify_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publish_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_item_navigation\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_hits\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_noauth\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urls_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"alternative_readmore\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"article_page_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publishing_options\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_article_options\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_urls_images_backend\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_urls_images_frontend\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_image\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_image_alt_txt\\\":