(104, 'com_content.article.24', '', '2024-05-24 02:53:41', 748, 5844, '344b63443115735d92e24aff4811ad2002549327', '{\"id\":\"24\",\"asset_id\":133,\"title\":\"Saliva Ejector Dental\",\"alias\":\"saliva-ejector-dental\",\"introtext\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 14px; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\\\">The saliva ejector, an essential tool in dental practice, efficiently removes excess saliva and fluids from the oral cavity during procedures. With its flexible and non-irritating design, it ensures patient comfort throughout treatment. This device aids in maintaining a clear field of view for the dentist, enhancing precision and efficiency during dental procedures. By effectively managing saliva and moisture, the saliva ejector contributes to a cleaner and more hygienic environment, reducing the risk of contamination and enhancing patient safety. Trust in the reliability and effectiveness of the saliva ejector for optimal dental care outcomes. D<\\/span><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">esigned to remove saliva, water, blood, and debris from the patient\'s mouth during dental procedures. It consists of a slender, flexible tube connected to a vacuum system, which generates suction to aspirate fluids from the oral cavity. Dental professionals rely on saliva ejectors to maintain a dry and clear field of view, enhancing visibility and facilitating efficient treatment delivery. The saliva ejector is typically positioned near the patient\'s cheek or tongue to capture fluids and prevent aspiration during procedures.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">During routine dental treatments such as cleanings, fillings, and extractions, saliva ejectors play a vital role in improving patient comfort and safety. By continuously removing excess moisture and debris, saliva ejectors help prevent gag reflexes and ensure a more pleasant experience for the patient. Moreover, the elimination of saliva and blood from the treatment area enhances the accuracy of dental procedures and reduces the risk of contamination, promoting optimal treatment outcomes. Dental professionals often utilize saliva ejectors in conjunction with other suction devices, such as high-volume evacuators, to maintain a clean and controlled working environment.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">In addition to their clinical utility, saliva ejectors contribute to infection control in dental settings by minimizing the spread of microorganisms and aerosols. The continuous suction provided by saliva ejectors helps capture and contain airborne particles generated during dental procedures, reducing the risk of cross-contamination between patients and dental staff. Dental practices adhere to strict sterilization protocols for saliva ejectors, ensuring that they are properly cleaned, disinfected, and disposed of after each use to prevent the transmission of infectious agents. Overall, saliva ejectors are indispensable tools in dental practice, promoting patient comfort, safety, and infection prevention while facilitating efficient and effective treatment delivery. In modern dentistry, saliva ejectors come in various designs and sizes to accommodate different patient needs and treatment requirements. Some saliva ejectors feature disposable tips for single-use applications, offering convenience and hygiene benefits by eliminating the need for sterilization between patients. Dental professionals often customize the positioning of saliva ejectors based on the specific procedure being performed and the patient\'s anatomy, ensuring optimal suction and comfort throughout the treatment. Additionally, advancements in suction technology continue to improve the efficiency and performance of saliva ejectors, enhancing their effectiveness in maintaining a clean and dry oral environment during dental procedures. As an integral part of dental practice, saliva ejectors contribute to the overall quality of patient care by supporting a safe, comfortable, and hygienic treatment experience.<\\/span><\\/p>\",\"fulltext\":\"\",\"state\":\"1\",\"catid\":8,\"created\":\"2024-05-04 06:33:22\",\"created_by\":\"748\",\"created_by_alias\":\"\",\"modified\":\"2024-05-24 02:53:41\",\"modified_by\":748,\"checked_out\":748,\"checked_out_time\":\"2024-05-24 02:53:34\",\"publish_up\":\"2024-05-04 06:33:22\",\"publish_down\":null,\"images\":\"{\\\"image_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_caption\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_caption\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"urls\":\"{\\\"urla\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlatext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targeta\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlbtext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlc\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlctext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetc\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"attribs\":\"{\\\"article_layout\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_titles\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_tags\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"info_block_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"info_block_show_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_create_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_modify_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publish_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_item_navigation\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_hits\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_noauth\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urls_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"alternative_readmore\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"article_page_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publishing_options\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_article_options\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_urls_images_backend\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_urls_images_frontend\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_image\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_image_alt_txt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_article_format\\\":\\\"standard\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_audio\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_gallery\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_video\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"version\":7,\"ordering\":1,\"metakey\":\"\",\"metadesc\":\"\",\"access\":1,\"hits\":1,\"metadata\":\"{\\\"robots\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"rights\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"featured\":\"0\",\"language\":\"*\",\"note\":\"\"}', 0),
(105, 'com_content.article.23', '', '2024-05-24 02:54:56', 748, 5237, '98e85875dbc220e41e749f6a5a01c942b5ff211b', '{\"id\":\"23\",\"asset_id\":132,\"title\":\"Anesthesia Needle\",\"alias\":\"dental-anesthesia-needle\",\"introtext\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">The anesthesia needle is a slender, hollow instrument used in medical procedures to deliver local anesthesia with precision and minimal discomfort. Featuring a sharp, beveled tip for smooth insertion, it ensures accurate delivery of the anesthetic solution to the targeted area. With its ultra-thin gauge and high-quality construction, it minimizes tissue trauma and patient discomfort during administration. Equipped with a hub for secure attachment to a syringe, it facilitates easy aspiration and injection of the anesthetic agent. Trusted by healthcare professionals worldwide, the anesthesia needle plays a crucial role in ensuring patient comfort and pain management during various medical and dental procedures.\\u00a0<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Also known as a dental syringe or local anesthetic syringe, is a crucial instrument in dentistry used for delivering local anesthesia to numb specific areas of the mouth during dental procedures. It typically consists of a stainless steel needle attached to a plastic or metal syringe barrel, allowing precise control and administration of the anesthetic solution. Dental professionals rely on anesthesia needles to provide pain relief and ensure patient comfort during various dental treatments, including fillings, extractions, root canals, and periodontal procedures. The anesthesia needle is designed to penetrate the soft tissues of the oral mucosa, allowing the anesthetic solution to be deposited near the nerves responsible for sensation in the targeted area.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">The design of anesthesia needles varies depending on factors such as gauge size, length, and bevel configuration, which can influence the speed and depth of anesthesia delivery. Common types of anesthesia needles include short needles for infiltrative anesthesia and long needles for nerve block anesthesia. Dental practitioners carefully select the appropriate needle and technique based on the specific procedure being performed and the patient\'s individual needs. Prior to administration, dental professionals often use topical anesthetic gel or spray to numb the injection site and minimize discomfort during needle insertion.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Despite advancements in dental technology and the availability of alternative anesthesia delivery methods, such as electronic anesthesia devices and needle-free systems, the anesthesia needle remains a widely used and effective tool in dentistry. Its simplicity, reliability, and cost-effectiveness make it a preferred choice for many dental procedures. Dental professionals adhere to strict infection control protocols when handling anesthesia needles, ensuring proper sterilization and disposal to prevent the transmission of infectious agents between patients. Overall, the anesthesia needle plays a vital role in modern dental practice, enabling clinicians to deliver safe and effective pain management solutions to enhance patient comfort and facilitate successful treatment outcomes.<\\/span><\\/p>\",\"fulltext\":\"\",\"state\":\"1\",\"catid\":8,\"created\":\"2024-05-04 06:31:51\",\"created_by\":\"748\",\"created_by_alias\":\"\",\"modified\":\"2024-05-24 02:54:56\",\"modified_by\":748,\"checked_out\":748,\"checked_out_time\":\"2024-05-24 02:54:27\",\"publish_up\":\"2024-05-04 06:31:51\",\"publish_down\":null,\"images\":\"{\\\"image_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_caption\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_caption\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"urls\":\"{\\\"urla\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlatext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targeta\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlbtext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlc\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlctext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetc\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"attribs\":\"{\\\"article_layout\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_titles\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_tags\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"info_block_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"info_block_show_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_create_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_modify_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publish_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_item_navigation\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_hits\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_noauth\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urls_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"alternative_readmore\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"article_page_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publishing_options\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_article_options\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_urls_images_backend\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_urls_images_frontend\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_image\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_image_alt_txt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_article_format\\\":\\\"standard\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_audio\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_gallery\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_video\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"version\":5,\"ordering\":2,\"metakey\":\"\",\"metadesc\":\"\",\"access\":1,\"hits\":0,\"metadata\":\"{\\\"robots\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"rights\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"featured\":\"0\",\"language\":\"*\",\"note\":\"\"}', 0),
(106, 'com_content.article.22', '', '2024-05-24 02:56:10', 748, 5185, 'b83134206b92efecbdb15087015f54948d293a7b', '{\"id\":\"22\",\"asset_id\":131,\"title\":\"Dental Cotton Roll\",\"alias\":\"dental-cotton-roll\",\"introtext\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">The dental cotton roll is a staple tool in dental practices worldwide, indispensable for maintaining a dry field during various procedures. Its cylindrical shape allows for easy placement and effective isolation of specific areas of the oral cavity. Made from soft and highly absorbent material, it efficiently absorbs saliva and moisture, enhancing the dentist\'s visibility and control. With its non-linting properties, it ensures a clean working environment and minimizes the risk of contamination. From routine cleanings to complex restorative work, the dental cotton roll is a versatile and essential component of every dental toolkit.\\u00a0<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Dental cotton rolls are essential items in dental practice, serving a variety of purposes to aid in moisture control, isolation, and patient comfort during dental procedures. These cylindrical rolls are made of absorbent cotton material and are available in various sizes to accommodate different clinical needs. Dental professionals commonly use cotton rolls to absorb saliva, blood, and other fluids from the oral cavity, ensuring a dry and clear field of view for accurate treatment delivery. The use of cotton rolls helps prevent contamination of dental instruments and materials, minimizing the risk of cross-infection between patients and ensuring optimal treatment outcomes.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">During restorative procedures such as fillings and crown preparations, dental cotton rolls are placed adjacent to the tooth being treated to isolate it from surrounding moisture and soft tissues. This isolation technique enhances the adhesion and longevity of dental restorations by providing a clean and dry surface for bonding materials. Additionally, cotton rolls are frequently used in conjunction with other isolation methods such as rubber dams to achieve comprehensive moisture control and isolation of the treatment area. By maintaining a dry operating field, dental cotton rolls contribute to the success and durability of dental restorations while improving the efficiency of dental procedures.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Furthermore, dental cotton rolls play a crucial role in enhancing patient comfort and safety during dental treatments. By absorbing excess saliva and fluids, cotton rolls help prevent gag reflexes and discomfort associated with moisture accumulation in the mouth. Dental professionals strategically place cotton rolls to protect delicate oral tissues from injury during procedures, such as preventing the tongue or cheek from being accidentally bitten or injured by dental instruments. Patients appreciate the use of cotton rolls for their role in minimizing discomfort and ensuring a more pleasant dental experience. Overall, dental cotton rolls are indispensable tools in dental practice, providing essential moisture control, isolation, and patient comfort to support successful treatment outcomes and promote overall oral health.<\\/span><\\/p>\",\"fulltext\":\"\",\"state\":\"1\",\"catid\":8,\"created\":\"2024-05-04 06:24:25\",\"created_by\":\"748\",\"created_by_alias\":\"\",\"modified\":\"2024-05-24 02:56:10\",\"modified_by\":748,\"checked_out\":748,\"checked_out_time\":\"2024-05-24 02:55:51\",\"publish_up\":\"2024-05-04 06:24:25\",\"publish_down\":null,\"images\":\"{\\\"image_intro\\\":\\\"\