(108, 'com_content.article.20', '', '2024-05-24 02:59:06', 748, 5384, 'eff501f3628f4bd0114c68772d80ba91309b2f29', '{\"id\":\"20\",\"asset_id\":129,\"title\":\"MicroBrush Applicator\",\"alias\":\"microbrush-applicator\",\"introtext\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 14px; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\\\">The microbrush applicator is a precise and versatile tool used in various medical and dental procedures for controlled application of materials in small or hard-to-reach areas. Featuring a fine, non-absorbent tip, it efficiently delivers solutions, adhesives, or medications with pinpoint accuracy, minimizing waste and ensuring precise placement. Its flexible yet sturdy handle offers optimal control and maneuverability, enhancing procedural efficiency and accuracy. With its disposable design, the microbrush applicator reduces the risk of cross-contamination and simplifies cleanup, making it a hygienic and convenient choice for healthcare settings. From dental bonding and sealant application to cosmetic procedures and wound care, the microbrush applicator is an indispensable instrument for achieving meticulous results.\\u00a0<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Microbrush applicators are small, disposable tools used in various dental procedures for precise application of materials such as adhesives, etchants, sealants, and bonding agents. These applicators consist of a microfiber tip attached to a flexible plastic handle, allowing dental professionals to access hard-to-reach areas with accuracy and control. Microbrushes come in different sizes and colors, with fine and ultrafine tips available to accommodate specific clinical needs and preferences. The versatility and ease of use of microbrush applicators make them invaluable instruments in dental practice, enhancing efficiency and precision in treatment delivery.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">During restorative procedures, microbrush applicators are commonly used to apply adhesive materials to tooth surfaces for bonding restorations such as composite fillings, veneers, and crowns. The fine, non-linting tips of microbrushes ensure uniform and consistent application of adhesive agents, promoting strong and durable bond formation between the restoration and the tooth structure. Additionally, microbrushes facilitate the application of etchants to prepare tooth surfaces for bonding by creating a microporous surface for enhanced adhesion. The disposable nature of microbrushes minimizes the risk of cross-contamination and simplifies cleanup, making them convenient and hygienic for single-use applications.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Furthermore, microbrush applicators find utility in various other dental procedures, including endodontic treatments, orthodontic bonding, and oral hygiene applications. In endodontics, microbrushes are used to deliver medicaments and sealers into root canals with precision, ensuring thorough disinfection and obturation. In orthodontics, microbrushes aid in the placement of adhesive materials for attaching brackets and bands to teeth, facilitating accurate bonding and alignment of orthodontic appliances. Additionally, microbrushes are used in oral hygiene procedures, such as applying fluoride varnish or sealants to protect teeth from decay and demineralization. Overall, microbrush applicators play a vital role in modern dental practice, offering versatility, precision, and convenience for a wide range of clinical applications.<\\/span><\\/p>\",\"fulltext\":\"\",\"state\":\"1\",\"catid\":8,\"created\":\"2024-05-04 06:18:59\",\"created_by\":\"748\",\"created_by_alias\":\"\",\"modified\":\"2024-05-24 02:59:06\",\"modified_by\":748,\"checked_out\":748,\"checked_out_time\":\"2024-05-24 02:58:35\",\"publish_up\":\"2024-05-04 06:18:59\",\"publish_down\":null,\"images\":\"{\\\"image_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_caption\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_caption\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"urls\":\"{\\\"urla\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlatext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targeta\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlbtext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlc\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlctext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetc\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"attribs\":\"{\\\"article_layout\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_titles\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_tags\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"info_block_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"info_block_show_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_create_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_modify_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publish_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_item_navigation\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_hits\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_noauth\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urls_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"alternative_readmore\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"article_page_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publishing_options\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_article_options\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_urls_images_backend\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_urls_images_frontend\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_image\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_image_alt_txt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_article_format\\\":\\\"standard\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_audio\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_gallery\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_video\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"version\":8,\"ordering\":5,\"metakey\":\"\",\"metadesc\":\"\",\"access\":1,\"hits\":1,\"metadata\":\"{\\\"robots\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"rights\\\":