(109, 'com_content.article.19', '', '2024-05-24 03:00:44', 748, 5101, '0f158dd5ab28877c0300112e3183df6b737897c1', '{\"id\":\"19\",\"asset_id\":128,\"title\":\"Instrument Kit\",\"alias\":\"disposable-instrument-kit\",\"introtext\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">The instruments kit is an essential component of any medical or dental practice, comprising a range of specialized tools tailored to specific procedures and treatments. From diagnostic instruments to surgical implements, each tool is carefully selected for its precision, durability, and ergonomic design. Organized in a compact and portable case, the instruments kit allows for easy access and convenient transport between patient appointments or clinical settings. With its diverse array of instruments, practitioners can confidently address a wide range of patient needs, from routine examinations to complex interventions. Whether in a clinic, hospital, or mobile healthcare unit, the instruments kit is an indispensable resource for delivering high-quality care to patients.\\u00a0<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 14px; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\\\">An instrument kit in dentistry is a collection of specialized tools and instruments carefully selected to meet the diverse needs of dental procedures. These kits typically contain a variety of hand instruments, rotary instruments, and accessories essential for performing specific treatments and tasks in dental practice. Dental instrument kits come in different configurations and sizes, tailored to different clinical specialties, such as restorative dentistry, periodontics, endodontics, oral surgery, and orthodontics. The contents of an instrument kit may vary depending on the specific procedures performed by the dental practitioner and the preferences of the dental team.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 14px; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\\\">In restorative dentistry, instrument kits often include hand instruments such as dental mirrors, explorers, probes, excavators, scalers, and composite placement instruments. These tools are essential for diagnosing dental caries, removing decayed tooth structure, preparing cavities, and placing restorative materials such as composite resin or amalgam. Rotary instruments such as high-speed and low-speed handpieces, burs, and polishing instruments may also be included in restorative instrument kits for efficient tooth preparation and finishing.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 14px; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\\\">In oral surgery, instrument kits typically contain a comprehensive array of instruments for procedures such as tooth extractions, dental implant placement, and bone grafting. These kits may include forceps, elevators, surgical burs, handpieces, sutures, and bone grafting materials, among other specialized instruments and accessories. The contents of oral surgery instrument kits are carefully curated to ensure that dental professionals have all the necessary tools at their disposal to perform safe and effective surgical interventions. Overall, instrument kits play a crucial role in facilitating efficient and successful dental procedures by providing dental professionals with the tools and equipment they need to deliver high-quality care to their patients.<\\/span><\\/p>\",\"fulltext\":\"\",\"state\":\"1\",\"catid\":8,\"created\":\"2024-05-04 06:16:09\",\"created_by\":\"748\",\"created_by_alias\":\"\",\"modified\":\"2024-05-24 03:00:44\",\"modified_by\":748,\"checked_out\":748,\"checked_out_time\":\"2024-05-24 02:59:32\",\"publish_up\":\"2024-05-04 06:16:09\",\"publish_down\":null,\"images\":\"{\\\"image_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_caption\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_caption\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"urls\":\"{\\\"urla\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlatext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targeta\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlbtext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlc\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlctext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetc\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"attribs\":\"{\\\"article_layout\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_titles\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_tags\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"info_block_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"info_block_show_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_create_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_modify_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publish_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_item_navigation\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_hits\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_noauth\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urls_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"alternative_readmore\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"article_page_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publishing_options\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_article_options\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_urls_images_backend\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_urls_images_frontend\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_image\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_image_alt_txt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_article_format\\\":\\\"standard\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_audio\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_gallery\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_video\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"version\":6,\"ordering\":6,\"metakey\":\"\",\"metadesc\":\"\",\"access\":1,\"hits\":0,\"metadata\":\"{\\\"robots\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"rights\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"featured\":\"0\",\"language\":\"*\",\"note\":\"\"}', 0),
(110, 'com_content.article.18', '', '2024-05-24 03:02:00', 748, 5212, '441656fec3a4c70353da0808e7a66060d34a998c', '{\"id\":\"18\",\"asset_id\":127,\"title\":\"Sterilization Pouches\",\"alias\":\"sterilization-pouches\",\"introtext\":\"<p><span style=\\\"font-size: 14px; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\\\">Sterilization pouches are essential tools used in medical and dental settings to maintain the sterility of instruments and equipment during storage and transportation. These pouches are designed with a combination of materials, typically including medical-grade paper and transparent film, to allow for effective sterilization and visibility of contents. The self-sealing feature of sterilization pouches ensures a secure closure, preventing contamination and maintaining sterility until the pouch is opened. They come in various sizes to accommodate different instruments and are compatible with most sterilization methods, including steam autoclaving and ethylene oxide sterilization. Trusted by healthcare professionals worldwide, sterilization pouches play a critical role in infection control protocols, safeguarding patient safety and promoting optimal healthcare outcomes.\\u00a0<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Essential components of infection control protocols in dental practice, providing a safe and effective means of sterilizing and storing dental instruments and equipment. These pouches are constructed from medical-grade materials, such as polypropylene or paper, and feature a self-sealing adhesive strip to ensure a secure closure. Sterilization pouches are designed to withstand the high temperatures and pressures of autoclave sterilization, effectively killing bacteria, viruses, and other pathogens to prevent cross-contamination between patients and dental staff. The transparent or semi-transparent design of sterilization pouches allows for easy identification of the enclosed instruments and facilitates visual inspection of the sterilization process.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Dental professionals rely on sterilization pouches to maintain the sterility of instruments from the moment they are processed through the autoclave until they are ready for use in patient care. The use of pouches helps prevent contamination of sterile instruments during storage and handling, ensuring that they remain safe and hygienic until needed for dental procedures. Additionally, sterilization pouches provide a convenient and organized method for storing sterilized instruments, helping dental practices comply with regulatory requirements and maintain efficient infection control practices.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Sterilization pouches come in various sizes to accommodate different types and sizes of dental instruments, from small hand instruments to larger rotary instruments and trays. Some pouches feature built-in indicators, such as chemical or heat-sensitive strips, to verify that proper sterilization conditions have been achieved during the autoclave cycle. Dental practices adhere to strict protocols for the proper loading, sealing, and labeling of sterilization pouches to ensure compliance with infection control standards and promote patient safety. Overall, sterilization pouches are indispensable tools in dental practice, providing a reliable and convenient solution for sterilizing, storing, and maintaining the sterility of dental instruments and equipment.<\\/span><\\/p>\",\"fulltext\":\"\",\"state\":\"1\",\"catid\":8,\"created\":\"2024-05-04 06:12:55\",\"created_by\":\"748\",\"created_by_alias\":\"\",\"modified\":\"2024-05-24 03:02:00\",\"modified_by\":748,\"checked_out\":748,\"checked_out_time\":\"2024-05-24 03:01:40\",\"publish_up\":\"2024-05-04 06:12:55\",\"publish_down\":null,\"images\":\"{\\\"image_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_caption\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_caption\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"urls\":\"{\\\"urla\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlatext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targeta\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlbtext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlc\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlctext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetc\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"attribs\":\"{\\\"article_layout\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_titles\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_tags\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"info_block_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"info_block_show_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_create_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_modify_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publish_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_item_navigation\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_hits\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_noauth\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urls_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"alternative_readmore\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"article_page_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publishing_options\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_article_options\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_urls_images_backend\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_urls_images_frontend\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_image\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_image_alt_txt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_article_format\\\":\\\"standard\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_audio\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_gallery\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_video\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"version\":6,\"ordering\":7,\"metakey\":\"\",\"metadesc\":\"\",\"access\":1,\"hits\":0,\"metadata\":\"{\\\"robots\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"rights\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"featured\":\"0\",\"language\":\"*\",\"note\":\"\"}', 0),
(111, 'com_content.article.17', '', '2024-05-24 03:03:33', 748, 4717, 'cb7ded9f54c5028ce41962760db95261dd9883f4', '{\"id\":\"17\",\"asset_id\":126,\"title\":\"Tissue Box\",\"alias\":\"tissue-box\",\"introtext\":\"<p><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">The tissue box is a household essential, providing convenient access to tissues for everyday use. Designed with functionality and aesthetics in mind, it typically features a rectangular shape with a top opening for easy tissue retrieval. Made from durable materials such as cardboard or plastic, the tissue box offers sturdiness and longevity. Its compact size allows for placement on countertops, desks, or tables, ensuring tissues are readily available wherever they\'re needed. With various designs and colors available, the tissue box adds a touch of practicality and style to any room d\\u00e9cor.\\u00a0<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Ubiquitous items found in dental offices, providing patients with convenient access to facial tissues for various purposes during their appointments. These boxes typically contain a stack of disposable tissues housed within a cardboard or plastic container, featuring a perforated opening for easy dispensing. Tissue boxes are strategically placed in dental operatories, waiting areas, and restroom facilities to ensure that patients can readily access tissues when needed. The availability of tissues serves multiple purposes, including wiping excess saliva, water, or dental materials from the face, cleaning hands, and providing comfort to patients during procedures.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">In dental practice, tissue boxes are essential for maintaining cleanliness and hygiene standards by facilitating the prompt disposal of used tissues and minimizing the spread of contaminants. Dental professionals encourage patients to use tissues to cover their mouths when coughing or sneezing, helping to reduce the risk of airborne transmission of respiratory droplets and pathogens. Additionally, tissues are provided to patients for wiping away excess saliva or water during dental procedures, enhancing patient comfort and facilitating clear communication between the patient and dental team.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">The design of tissue boxes often incorporates features that promote convenience and ease of use, such as pop-up dispensers or decorative packaging that complements the aesthetic of the dental office. Some tissue boxes are equipped with antimicrobial coatings or additives to inhibit the growth of bacteria and maintain a hygienic environment. Dental practices routinely restock tissue boxes to ensure that patients always have access to clean tissues throughout their visit. Overall, tissue boxes are essential accessories in dental offices, contributing to patient comfort, hygiene, and infection control while enhancing the overall experience of dental care.<\\/span><\\/p>\",\"fulltext\":\"\",\"state\":\"1\",\"catid\":10,\"created\":\"2024-05-04 05:33:06\",\"created_by\":\"748\",\"created_by_alias\":\"\",\"modified\":\"2024-05-24 03:03:33\",\"modified_by\":748,\"checked_out\":748,\"checked_out_time\":\"2024-05-24 03:03:10\",\"publish_up\":\"2024-05-04 05:33:06\",\"publish_down\":null,\"images\":\"{\\\"image_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_caption\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_caption\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"urls\":\"{\\\"urla\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlatext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targeta\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlbtext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlc\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlctext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetc\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"a