(116, 'com_content.article.13', '', '2024-05-24 03:08:39', 748, 5380, '07541ca6bcf77245fd98d376b510e01c870691bc', '{\"id\":\"13\",\"asset_id\":122,\"title\":\"Dental Sander Gun\",\"alias\":\"dental-chair\",\"introtext\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">The dental sander gun is a specialized instrument used in dental laboratories for precise shaping and contouring of dental prostheses and restorations. It employs compressed air to deliver a stream of abrasive particles, such as aluminum oxide or diamond grit, onto the surface of dental materials. With its ergonomic design and adjustable settings, the sander gun allows technicians to achieve fine detailing and smooth finishes on various dental materials, including ceramics and acrylics. Its controlled abrasion process enables technicians to refine margins, adjust occlusion, and enhance aesthetic outcomes with accuracy and efficiency. Trusted by dental professionals for its versatility and reliability, the dental sander gun is an essential tool in the fabrication of high-quality dental restorations. <\\/span><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">It appears there might be a confusion regarding the term \\\"dental sander gun\\\" as it doesn\'t seem to correspond to a recognized dental tool or device. However, I can provide information on dental sandblasting units, which are commonly used in dental laboratories for various purposes.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Dental sandblasting units, also known as dental sanders or sandblasters, are specialized devices used in dental laboratories for surface preparation, cleaning, and texturing of dental prostheses, restorations, and appliances. These units typically consist of a compressed air source, an abrasive material chamber, and a handpiece with a nozzle for directing the abrasive stream onto the dental workpiece. The abrasive material, often aluminum oxide or silica particles, is propelled at high velocity through the nozzle onto the surface of the dental material, effectively removing contaminants, residues, and surface irregularities.<\\/span><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">sandblasting units are commonly used to enhance the bond strength of dental materials by creating a roughened surface texture that promotes mechanical interlocking between the restoration and adhesive agents. For example, sandblasting is often performed on metal frameworks for ceramic restorations, dental implants, and orthodontic appliances to improve the retention and durability of the final restoration. Additionally, sandblasting units are utilized for cleaning and polishing dental prostheses, removing investment materials from castings, and adjusting the fit and contour of dental appliances.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">The use of dental sandblasting units requires skill and precision to achieve optimal results without causing damage to the dental workpiece. Dental technicians must carefully control the pressure, angle, and duration of the sandblasting process to avoid over-abrasion or surface roughness that could compromise the integrity of the restoration. Proper maintenance and calibration of sandblasting equipment are also essential to ensure consistent performance and prolong the lifespan of the device. Overall, dental sandblasting units are valuable tools in dental laboratories, offering versatility, efficiency, and precision in the preparation and finishing of dental restorations and appliances.<\\/span><\\/p>\",\"fulltext\":\"\",\"state\":\"1\",\"catid\":10,\"created\":\"2024-05-04 05:10:00\",\"created_by\":\"748\",\"created_by_alias\":\"\",\"modified\":\"2024-05-24 