(120, 'com_content.article.10', '', '2024-05-24 03:12:42', 748, 5676, '3f86b0aba2b7dda86a67fcb58f5cdd8cc9c2bae8', '{\"id\":\"10\",\"asset_id\":119,\"title\":\"Dental Clean Scaler\",\"alias\":\"dental-clean-scaler\",\"introtext\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size: 14px; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\\\">A dental scaler is a handheld instrument used by dental professionals to remove plaque, tartar, and calculus deposits from the teeth and along the gum line. Equipped with a pointed tip or curved blade, the scaler gently but effectively scrapes away hardened deposits without damaging the tooth enamel or surrounding tissues. Dental scalers come in various designs, including manual scalers and ultrasonic scalers, each offering unique benefits and applications. With precise control and ergonomic handles, dental scalers allow for thorough cleaning and polishing, promoting oral health and preventing gum disease. Trusted by dentists worldwide, dental scalers are essential tools in routine dental cleanings and periodontal treatments.\\u00a0<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Essential tools used by dental professionals to remove plaque, tartar, and stains from the teeth and gums during dental cleanings and periodontal procedures. These scalers are designed to safely and effectively remove deposits from the tooth surface and below the gumline, helping to prevent oral diseases such as gingivitis and periodontitis. Dental cleaning scalers come in various shapes and sizes, each with specific features and functionalities tailored to different clinical needs and treatment objectives.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">One of the most commonly used types of dental cleaning scalers is the ultrasonic scaler, which utilizes high-frequency vibrations to break up and remove plaque and calculus from the teeth. Ultrasonic scalers consist of a handpiece connected to a power unit, which generates ultrasonic vibrations through a thin metal tip or insert. The rapid vibration of the scaler tip creates cavitation bubbles in the water stream, which disrupt plaque biofilm and dislodge tartar deposits without causing damage to the tooth surface. Ultrasonic scalers offer advantages such as reduced treatment time, improved patient comfort, and enhanced access to hard-to-reach areas compared to traditional hand scalers.<\\/span><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">In addition to ultrasonic scalers, dental cleaning kits may include hand scalers or curettes, which are handheld instruments with sharp, curved tips used for manual removal of plaque and calculus. Hand scalers come in various designs, such as sickle scalers, universal curettes, and gracey curettes, each with specific blade shapes and angles optimized for different tooth surfaces and periodontal conditions. Dental professionals utilize hand scalers to meticulously remove calculus deposits from the tooth surface and root surfaces, particularly in areas where ultrasonic scalers may be less effective or contraindicated.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Dental cleaning scalers play a crucial role in maintaining oral health and preventing periodontal diseases by effectively removing plaque and calculus from the teeth and gums. Proper selection and use of dental scalers require skill, technique, and knowledge of periodontal anatomy to ensure thorough cleaning while minimizing trauma to the soft tissues. Dental professionals adhere to strict infection control protocols when handling and sterilizing scalers to prevent cross-contamination between patients and ensure patient safety. Overall, dental cleaning scalers are indispensable tools in dental practice, contributing to optimal oral hygiene and periodontal health for patients of all ages.<\\/span><\\/p>\",\"fulltext\":\"\",\"state\":\"1\",\"catid\":10,\"created\":\"2024-05-04 04:57:13\",\"created_by\":\"748\",\"created_by_alias\":\"\",\"modified\":\"2024-05-24 03:12:42\",\"modified_by\":748,\"checked_out\":748,\"checked_out_time\":\"2024-05-24 03:12:13\",\"publish_up\":\"2024-05-04 04:57:13\",\"publish_down\":null,\"images\":\"{\\\"image_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_caption\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_caption\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"urls\":\"{\\\"urla\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlatext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targeta\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlbtext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlc\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlctext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetc\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"attribs\":\"{\\\"article_layout\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_titles\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_tags\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"info_block_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"info_block_show_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_parent_category\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"link_author\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_create_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_modify_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publish_date\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_item_navigation\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_hits\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_noauth\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urls_position\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"alternative_readmore\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"article_page_title\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_publishing_options\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_article_options\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_urls_images_backend\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"show_urls_images_frontend\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_image\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_image_alt_txt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"helix_ultimate_article_format\\\":\\\"st